---
target: cli
version: 1
validations:
  - name: main-go-exists
    type: file_check
    path: main.go
    contains:
      - "package main"
      - "cmd.Execute"

  - name: root-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/root.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"
      - "rootCmd"
      - "cobra.Command"

  - name: init-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/init.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"
      - "initCmd"

  - name: build-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/build.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"
      - "buildCmd"
      - "--output"
      - "profile"

  - name: clean-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/clean.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"

  - name: validate-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/validate.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"

  - name: status-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/status.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"

  - name: commit-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/commit.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"
      - "intent:"
      - "generated:"

  - name: check-command-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/cmd/check.go
    contains:
      - "package cmd"
      - "ValidateAllSpecs"

  - name: add-command-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -rl "add.*intent\|add.*validation" src/cmd/*.go | wc -l
    exit_code: 0

  - name: list-command-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -rl "list.*intent\|list.*validation\|list.*profile" src/cmd/*.go | wc -l
    exit_code: 0

  - name: go-mod-exists
    type: file_check
    path: go.mod
    contains:
      - "module github.com/pboueri/intentc"
      - "github.com/spf13/cobra"

  - name: binary-builds
    type: command_check
    command: go build -o /dev/null .
    exit_code: 0

  - name: all-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: go test ./...
    exit_code: 0

  - name: cli-no-globals
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that CLI commands follow proper dependency injection:
      1. No global agent, builder, or state manager instances
      2. Each command function creates its own dependencies
      3. Config is loaded per-command, not globally cached
      4. The only globals are Cobra command definitions and flag variables
    severity: warning
    context_files: ["src/cmd/*.go"]

  - name: init-creates-structure
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the init command:
      1. Creates .intentc/ directory with config.yaml containing a default agent profile
      2. Creates intent/ directory
      3. Creates a template project.ic with valid YAML frontmatter (name, version, tags)
      4. Adds .intentc/state/ to .gitignore
      5. Errors if already initialized
      6. Errors if not in a git repository
      7. The generated config.yaml has a "default" profile with provider "claude"
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/cmd/init.go"]

  - name: commit-separates-intent-and-generated
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the commit command:
      1. Separates intent/ files from generated files
      2. Creates separate commits with "intent:" and "generated:" prefixes
      3. Only commits staged/changed files (doesn't commit everything blindly)
      4. Handles the case where only intent files changed, or only generated files changed
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/cmd/commit.go"]
  - name: check-runs-schema-validation
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the check command:
      1. Calls parser.ValidateAllSpecs to validate all spec files against schemas
      2. Calls config.ValidateConfig to validate the config file
      3. Reports schema violations with file path, field, and description
      4. Separates errors from warnings in output
      5. Exits with code 1 if any error-severity violations found
      6. Prints "All spec files are valid." only when everything passes
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/cmd/check.go"]

  - name: build-uses-profile
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the build command uses agent profiles:
      1. Accepts --profile flag for profile selection
      2. Resolves profile from config via config.GetProfile
      3. Creates agent via agent.CreateFromProfile (not CreateFromConfig)
      4. Passes ProfileName through BuildOptions to the builder
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/cmd/build.go"]
---

# CLI Validations

The CLI is the user-facing surface of intentc. It must build, all tests must pass, and commands must follow the dependency injection pattern (no globals). The commit command's separation of intent and generated changes is a critical correctness requirement. The check command must perform full schema validation, and the build/validate commands must use agent profiles.
